# Preliminaries of a Decentralized network

## Digital Heritage Pod (Erfgoedpod)

The Digital Heritage Pod serves an institution's main exchangehub for sharing cultural heritage information with external service providers and other institutions.

We start from the basis Solid design defined in the [Solid specification](https://solid.github.io/specification/).

The basic architecture of a Solid pod consists of:

- Datastore: a file-system and/or database populated by information (eg. datasets, descriptions of datasets, organisation profiles) from the Collections Management System and Digital Asset Management system
- ACL layer: controls access to the contents of the datastore
- Inbox: receive Linked Data notifications from other actors
- LDP API: exposes the data and the inbox layer/file-system

